According to the very detailed last will
of Arthur Schnitzler, his diaries must not
be read by anybody, not even by his son
Heinrich, who is an actor and stages plays
in Berlin. His diaries until 1899 must not
be published until twenty years after his
death, the others not until forty.
autobiography must not appear for twenty
years, and without any alterations or cuts.
Among his papers are some one-act
plays, which Schnitzler did not allow to
be performed during his lifetime, for per¬
sonal and artistic reasons; an almost com¬
plete MS. of the play, “ The Word” (“ Pro¬
cession of Shadows" is its other title); and
some drafts of a drama dealing with the
period of the Thirty Years' War.
